人事動態




第31期出刊日：2017.03.31




新進教師介紹

 



物理學系 謝馬利歐副教授


學歷： 
                          Ph.D. in Electrical  Engineering, Massachusetts Institute of Technology, USA, 2011
                          M.S. in Electrical  Engineering, Massachusetts Institute of Technology, USA, 2011
                          M.S., Applied Physics ,  TU Ilmenau, Germany, 2006
                          B.S., Applied Physics ,  TU Ilmenau, Germany, 2006
經歷：
  Since 2017-2 Professor in Physics, NTU.  
2012-2017 Assistant Professor in Materials Science, National Cheng Kung  University
2011-2012 Postdoctoral researcher, National Taiwan University
專長與個人介紹： 
                          My  research focuses on nanostructures, i.e. arrangements whose properties are  fundamentally changed when their size reaches the atomic scale. One example for  this astonishing transition can be found in graphene – a carbon sheet that is  only one atom thick. Different from its bulk counterpart, graphite, it exhibits  a unique band structure where electrons behave like massless particles – a  condition that is akin to light. Nanostructures not only exhibit new properties  that my lab is trying to understand but these properties can be significantly  altered when they are brought in contact with other materials. Graphene, for  example, turns from a conductor to a semiconductor on top of different metal  contacts. Therefore, a first focus of my lab is the production of  nanostructures and the adjustment of their properties. We have recently shown  the scalable synthesis of graphene and the modification of their properties  using electrochemical techniques. Furthermore, we demonstrated that the  conversion of graphene from pristine to semiconducting behavior is a reversible  process that does not rely on chemical modification as previously assumed.

The  wide range of new behavior in nanostructures and our ability to change them  makes nanostructures promising for diverse applications. We have demonstrated  the use of graphene in highly efficient light sensors and bio-sensors. The most  attractive use of ultrathin nanostructures, however, is in combination with  other materials. These heterojunctions enable new current-transport modes where  current goes through an insulating nanostructure rather than around it. We have  applied this behavior in new transistors, that combine low cost with high  performance and light emitters that can emit any arbitrary color.

My team  is relocating from Tainan, where we worked for 5 years in Cheng Kung University  and we are looking forward to making new connections with researchers in  National Taiwan University.
 


海洋研究所 曾於恆教授


學歷： 
美國史丹福大學土木及環境工程研究所博士 
美國史丹福大學機械工程研究所碩士 
臺灣大學機械工程研究所學士 
經歷：
  美國約翰霍普金斯大學機械工程系博士後 
  美國勞倫斯柏克萊國家實驗室博士後 
  臺灣大學大氣科學系助理教授 
  臺灣大學大氣科學系副教授 
  美國國家大氣研究中心科學家
  臺灣大學海洋研究所教授 
專長：
  海洋大氣數值模擬、地球系統模式、海氣交互作用、海洋氣候動力、紊流模擬及高效能平行計算
個人介紹：
  迴首過去二十年的因緣際會，機械系畢業後一開始原執著於醫學流體更新一層的認知，然而由於博士指導教授研究計畫方向的拓展，從工程領域的紊流模擬逐漸轉移到海洋、大氣各種尺度數值模型的發展以及模式與觀測實驗的結合，所有新領域的接觸與學習過程大大開啟了我的眼界，擴展出更開闊但專一的研究路線，由微小尺度的流體動力模擬逐漸轉移到大尺度的氣候變遷，體驗到所有自然界萬物律動的脈動背後都深藏著值得我們深入理解的奧秘，若能夠有效利用科學計算應用在這些領域也能進一步的改進人類與大自然的互動!
其實從心臟模擬到大氣海洋動力過程探討這一路走來，一直瞭解如何完整的利用數值計算模擬大自然萬物的變化就是一件吃力不討好的工作，我們就像未知的孩子，渴望學習不斷摸索，而模式軟體的研發在未正式完成前更是一段長期寂寞的過程，需要能夠忍受沒有成果的蟄伏，向前邁進更不是一蹴可及，甚至是一段充滿不確定性各種知識經驗不斷地累積，五年前抱著感恩的心情離開臺大大氣繫到全球大氣相關研究領域最著名的國家大氣研究中心直接參與美國最新一代氣候模式內海洋動力相關研發工作，感謝同仁背後的大力支持，那裏至今仍是主導全球氣候模式研發的聖地，當我們決定走到研究教學的路線之後，我們就是不斷再學習不斷成長，而這些日子的努力也慢慢有些代價，現在重新回來臺大，更期許自己重新再出發之時能夠逐漸奠立臺灣自主進行海洋氣候模型研發工作一個創新的里程碑。                       


 





 























